# Change Specification: epistemic-session-race

## Summary

Replace the single-file `~/.claude/.current-session` marker with per-PPID markers under `~/.claude/.current-session/` (directory), keyed by Claude main process PID and storing Claude Code's own `session_id` from SessionStart stdin JSON, plus a shared `epistemic_get_session_id` helper used by every reader — eliminating cross-session clobber that has caused 3 confirmed incidents on 2026-05-01 (including one during planning of this fix).

## What Changes

### Files/Components Touched

| File | Nature of Change |
|------|------------------|
| `scripts/epistemic-marker.sh` | **NEW** — shared helper: `epistemic_marker_path`, `epistemic_get_session_id`, `epistemic_sweep_orphans` |
| `hooks/epistemic-preflight.sh` | Modify — read stdin JSON for session_id, write per-PPID marker via helper, sweep stale PIDs on entry, handle `source: "resume"` |
| `hooks/epistemic-postflight.sh` | Modify — read per-PPID marker via helper (stdin fallback), scope `rm -f` to own marker only |
| `hooks/_audit-log.sh` | Modify — source helper, resolve session_id via `epistemic_get_session_id` |
| `commands/epistemic-preflight.md` | Modify — bash block reads marker via helper |
| `commands/epistemic-postflight.md` | Modify — bash block reads marker via helper, scoped delete |
| `commands/end.md` | Modify — bash block reads marker via helper |
| `commands/start.md` | Modify — bash block reads marker via helper |
